The paper discusses a method for efficient sampling from continuous distributions using stochastic gradient Hamiltonian Monte Carlo (SGHMC) and introduces a novel second-order SG-MCMC algorithm. The paper also applies the proposed method to Bayesian logistic regression and Bayesian neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.ML (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves statistical analysis and convergence rate analysis, which suggests the sub-categories cs.ST (Statistics) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as possible sub-categories.
